# Problem 3. Present Delivery

_Santa has limited time to drop at least some presents for each house. Help him with his mission!_

You will receive a **string** with **even integers** separated by **&quot;@&quot;** representing each house with its **number of members** and a series of **Jump** commands until you receive **&quot;Merry Xmas!&quot;**

Santa starts at the position of the **first** house and has to jump by a **given length.** The jump command will be in format: **&quot;Jump {length}&quot;**.

Each time he jumps from one house to another he drops **2 presents** for that house and **decreases** the needed presents for that house. If Santa jumps on a house which **doesn&#39;t need** more presents (presents = 0) you should instead print &quot; **House {houseIndex} will have a Merry Christmas.**&quot;.

Keep in mind that Santa can have a **bigger jump length** than the **size of the field** and if he does jump **outside** of it he should **start** from the **beginning** again **.**

_For example we have a field of size 3 and each house has 6 members. Santa is at the start and jumps with length of 2. He will end up at index 2 and decrease the needed presents by 2 (6 – 2 = 4). Next he jumps again with length of 2 and ends up at index position 1 and again decreases the needed presents__._

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

## Input

- On the first line you will receive a **string** with **even integers** separated by **&quot;@&quot;**  **–** houses and their number of members.
- On the next lines until &quot; **Merry Xmas!**&quot; you will receive jump commands in format: &quot; **Jump {length}**&quot;.

## Output

At the end print Santa&#39;s **last position** and whether or **not** his mission was successful:

- &quot; **Santa&#39;s last position was {**** lastPositionIndex ****}.**&quot;
- If **all members** of **each house** have presents print:
  - **oo**&quot; **Mission was successful.**&quot;
- If **not** print the **count** of all houses that **won&#39;t** have a Merry Christmas:
  - **oo****&quot; ****Santa has failed {**** housesCount ****} houses****.&quot;**

## Constraints

- The **field** can be of size **[1…20]**

- Each **house** will have an **even number** of   **members** [**2** … **10**]
- Each **jump length** will be an integer [**1** … **20**]

## Examples

| **Input** | **Output** |
| --- | --- |
| 10@10@10@2Jump 1Jump 2Merry Xmas! | Santa&#39;s last position was 3.Santa has failed 3 houses. |
| 2@4@2Jump 2Jump 2Jump 8Jump 3Jump 1Merry Xmas! | House 0 will have a Merry Christmas.Santa&#39;s last position was 1.Mission was successful. |
